# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorPath4
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Hours had passed since she slayed the beast."
    new "Hours had passed since she slayed the beast."

    old "Sarah sat slumped against one of the great pillars that kept up the roof of the throne room of Bagrad palace."
    new "Sarah sat slumped against one of the great pillars that kept up the roof of the throne room of Bagrad palace."

    old "The room had felt vast, empty and cold, but it was now filled with the conquerors of Bagrad."
    new "The room had felt vast, empty and cold, but it was now filled with the conquerors of Bagrad."

    old "Mythran soldiers, her own fellow mercenaries, everyone who had participated in the battle was here."
    new "Mythran soldiers, her own fellow mercenaries, everyone who had participated in the battle was here."

    old "With any threat of resistance now crushed, the soldier's on all sides had put down their swords and picked up their wine bottles."
    new "With any threat of resistance now crushed, the soldier's on all sides had put down their swords and picked up their wine bottles."

    old "Most everyone she saw was either drunk or blacked out."
    new "Most everyone she saw was either drunk or blacked out."

    old "All across the room, random groups of soldiers mingled around campfires, as the host of soldiers feasted upon what had once been the contents of the royal kitchen."
    new "All across the room, random groups of soldiers mingled around campfires, as the host of soldiers feasted upon what had once been the contents of the royal kitchen."

    old "Entire hogs, glistened and crackled as the flames of campfires licked at the meat and gristle, turning it a shiny deep brown."
    new "Entire hogs, glistened and crackled as the flames of campfires licked at the meat and gristle, turning it a shiny deep brown."

    old "Sarah had her fill, both of wine and food."
    new "Sarah had her fill, both of wine and food."

    old "So too did she have her fill of praise. There must have barely been a single soldier who hadn't stopped her and asked her about killing the beast."
    new "So too did she have her fill of praise. There must have barely been a single soldier who hadn't stopped her and asked her about killing the beast."

    old "Those who had been present in the throne room had managed to turn the story of her killing the beast into a tale larger than life."
    new "Those who had been present in the throne room had managed to turn the story of her killing the beast into a tale larger than life."

    old "Perhaps it was."
    new "Perhaps it was."

    old "Staring out across the room, Sarah felt oddly content."
    new "Staring out across the room, Sarah felt oddly content."

    old "Each campaign brought with it the risk of death. But despite everything, she had survived another."
    new "Each campaign brought with it the risk of death. But despite everything, she had survived another."

    old "Sarah turned her head slowly."
    new "Sarah turned her head slowly."

    old "Hey. Thought I missed you out here."
    new "Hey. Thought I missed you out here."

    old "Miss a chance to see the great hero that killed a demon? I'd never."
    new "Miss a chance to see the great hero that killed a demon? I'd never."

    old "I didn't kill a demon."
    new "I didn't kill a demon."

    old "Maybe. Whose to say it wasn't. You know what a demon looks like?"
    new "Maybe. Whose to say it wasn't. You know what a demon looks like?"

    old "It was hard to argue for Sarah. Maybe the thing had been a demon, what did she really know about such things?"
    new "It was hard to argue for Sarah. Maybe the thing had been a demon, what did she really know about such things?"

    old "Whatever. If you're here to shove another compliment up my ass, know that I've had my fill."
    new "Whatever. If you're here to shove another compliment up my ass, know that I've had my fill."

    old "She saw Kate grin in that mischievous way of hers."
    new "She saw Kate grin in that mischievous way of hers."

    old "Ooh, your ass is stuffed huh?"
    new "Ooh, your ass is stuffed huh?"

    old "You're vile Kate, you really are."
    new "You're vile Kate, you really are."

    old "I know you longer than just about anyone else here."
    new "I know you longer than just about anyone else here."

    old "I remember the girl that started crying because she got her head stuck in a rabbit's burrow and couldn't get it out."
    new "I remember the girl that started crying because she got her head stuck in a rabbit's burrow and couldn't get it out."

    old "That wasn't funny!"
    new "That wasn't funny!"

    old "I think it was."
    new "I think it was."

    old "You've always been the one to get me into trouble."
    new "You've always been the one to get me into trouble."

    old "Maybe. But I was also the one to pull you out of that burrow, remember? So I guess it even out."
    new "Maybe. But I was also the one to pull you out of that burrow, remember? So I guess it even out."

    old "Sarah couldn't help but laugh."
    new "Sarah couldn't help but laugh."

    old "Well, I managed to get myself into plenty of trouble lately. But the thing from today that was..."
    new "Well, I managed to get myself into plenty of trouble lately. But the thing from today that was..."

    old "Sarah could see Kate grew more somber."
    new "Sarah could see Kate grew more somber."

    old "Sarah, I...when I heard the screams coming from the throne room, I thought I'd lose you..."
    new "Sarah, I...when I heard the screams coming from the throne room, I thought I'd lose you..."

    old "Everything has just been a blur since then...I've barely had time to process it."
    new "Everything has just been a blur since then...I've barely had time to process it."

    old "Hell, that thing still doesn't seem real..."
    new "Hell, that thing still doesn't seem real..."

    old "You have any idea what it was?"
    new "You have any idea what it was?"

    old "Never seen anything like it. Never even read about anything like it. All I know is that the Shah summoned it, somehow."
    new "Never seen anything like it. Never even read about anything like it. All I know is that the Shah summoned it, somehow."

    old "He summoned it?"
    new "He summoned it?"

    old "He was using some kind of...dagger. I don't know. It all happened so fast."
    new "He was using some kind of...dagger. I don't know. It all happened so fast."

    old "Kate patted Sarah on the shoulders."
    new "Kate patted Sarah on the shoulders."

    old "Whatever. I find it best not to worry too long about shit that's way beyond my ability to understand, and you shouldn't either."
    new "Whatever. I find it best not to worry too long about shit that's way beyond my ability to understand, and you shouldn't either."

    old "As for the Shah, he got what he deserved for playing with dark magic."
    new "As for the Shah, he got what he deserved for playing with dark magic."

    old "In the moment after Sarah had killed the beast, the mob of soldiers had rushed towards her in celebration, but more accurately, there had been two mobs."
    new "In the moment after Sarah had killed the beast, the mob of soldiers had rushed towards her in celebration, but more accurately, there had been two mobs."

    old "The one that raised up Sarah and sung her praises, and the other, smaller group of soldiers, that had rushed the dais and seized the Shah."
    new "The one that raised up Sarah and sung her praises, and the other, smaller group of soldiers, that had rushed the dais and seized the Shah."

    old "His laughing never stopped."
    new "His laughing never stopped."

    old "Not even when she had killed the beast."
    new "Not even when she had killed the beast."

    old "Not even when the soldiers had grabbed him and begun to stomp him to death."
    new "Not even when the soldiers had grabbed him and begun to stomp him to death."

    old "She could still hear his cheerful madness, turning towards a gurgle as he choked on his own blood and bones."
    new "She could still hear his cheerful madness, turning towards a gurgle as he choked on his own blood and bones."

    old "Still, Sarah could hardly feel sorry for the man."
    new "Still, Sarah could hardly feel sorry for the man."

    old "He had lost, but rather than accept defeat, played around with powers beyond his understanding."
    new "He had lost, but rather than accept defeat, played around with powers beyond his understanding."

    old "Good men had died for no reason, other than an arrogant man's vanity."
    new "Good men had died for no reason, other than an arrogant man's vanity."

    old "Yeah, he got what he deserved."
    new "Yeah, he got what he deserved."

    old "Wish I'd been there to see it though. The stories people are telling, sounds like you were incredible."
    new "Wish I'd been there to see it though. The stories people are telling, sounds like you were incredible."

    old "Don't believe everything they tell you. Soldier's can be worse than midwives when it comes to telling tall tales."
    new "Don't believe everything they tell you. Soldier's can be worse than midwives when it comes to telling tall tales."

    old "Ain't that the truth."
    new "Ain't that the truth."

    old "For a moment, the two sat in silence."
    new "For a moment, the two sat in silence."

    old "Sarah could feel there was more that Kate wanted to say."
    new "Sarah could feel there was more that Kate wanted to say."

    old "Ask Kate to come to your room tonight"
    new "Ask Kate to come to your room tonight"

    old "Sarah broke the silence."
    new "Sarah broke the silence."

    old "Tonight, after the party. There's some things I might want to discuss with you."
    new "Tonight, after the party. There's some things I might want to discuss with you."

    old "So if you could...wait for me in my room?"
    new "So if you could...wait for me in my room?"

    old "Sarah could see a smile on Kate's face."
    new "Sarah could see a smile on Kate's face."

    old "Of course, commander. I'd never disobey an order like that."
    new "Of course, commander. I'd never disobey an order like that."

    old "Kate made an unserious attempt at a salute and turned to walk away."
    new "Kate made an unserious attempt at a salute and turned to walk away."

    old "Sarah waved her off as she stayed behind, seated against the pillar."
    new "Sarah waved her off as she stayed behind, seated against the pillar."

    old "Don't say anything to Kate"
    new "Don't say anything to Kate"

    old "The silence lingered."
    new "The silence lingered."

    old "After a while, Kate was the first to move."
    new "After a while, Kate was the first to move."

    old "Well, Sarah, I need to go meet up with some of my men, I promised I'd play bone-dice with them."
    new "Well, Sarah, I need to go meet up with some of my men, I promised I'd play bone-dice with them."

    old "Don't let them rob you like they always do."
    new "Don't let them rob you like they always do."

    old "Hey! I win...sometimes."
    new "Hey! I win...sometimes."

    old "Anyway, I'll see you around. And try to enjoy the party a bit."
    new "Anyway, I'll see you around. And try to enjoy the party a bit."

    old "Kate waved as she walked away, and Sarah waved back at her."
    new "Kate waved as she walked away, and Sarah waved back at her."

    old "Alone again, Sarah continued to look out over the party."
    new "Alone again, Sarah continued to look out over the party."

    old "Half a bottle of wine sat idle besides her."
    new "Half a bottle of wine sat idle besides her."

    old "Sarah could already feel her eyes floating across the room, hard to focus because of the alcohol."
    new "Sarah could already feel her eyes floating across the room, hard to focus because of the alcohol."

    old "Everybody looked so happy."
    new "Everybody looked so happy."

    old "But beneath their feet, a mountain of misery."
    new "But beneath their feet, a mountain of misery."

    old "Sarah knew that beyond the palace, gangs of soldiers, some Mythran, some from her own mercenary company, would be stalking the streets."
    new "Sarah knew that beyond the palace, gangs of soldiers, some Mythran, some from her own mercenary company, would be stalking the streets."

    old "Looking for women, those willing and unwilling."
    new "Looking for women, those willing and unwilling."

    old "Homes would be looted. Those who resisted, killed, and sometimes even those who didn't resist."
    new "Homes would be looted. Those who resisted, killed, and sometimes even those who didn't resist."

    old "A great city was being put to the sword, and she had played a part in it."
    new "A great city was being put to the sword, and she had played a part in it."

    old "Sarah did what she always did when it felt as though the burdens of her life were becoming too much."
    new "Sarah did what she always did when it felt as though the burdens of her life were becoming too much."

    old "She closed her eyes and dreamed of Rosanna."
    new "She closed her eyes and dreamed of Rosanna."

    old "Her nation, far across the sea."
    new "Her nation, far across the sea."

    old "Home."
    new "Home."

    old "A place to which she would return."
    new "A place to which she would return."

    old "Bring justice to those that had ruined her family, her ancestral homeland."
    new "Bring justice to those that had ruined her family, her ancestral homeland."

    old "And she, she would be the one to deliver that justice."
    new "And she, she would be the one to deliver that justice."

    old "But in her dreams, she never thought of the violence."
    new "But in her dreams, she never thought of the violence."

    old "Instead, she dreamed of herself standing on the fields, just outside of the capital."
    new "Instead, she dreamed of herself standing on the fields, just outside of the capital."

    old "Behind her, Castle Reinmeer, standing out above the city."
    new "Behind her, Castle Reinmeer, standing out above the city."

    old "In front of her, the endless fields of grass that danced in the motions of the wind."
    new "In front of her, the endless fields of grass that danced in the motions of the wind."

    old "If you watched for long enough, it could begin to feel like an ocean of green."
    new "If you watched for long enough, it could begin to feel like an ocean of green."

    old "As though you were all alone in the world. And nothing could go wrong."
    new "As though you were all alone in the world. And nothing could go wrong."

    old "It was worth it."
    new "It was worth it."

    old "Everything she was doing was worth it. Sarah repeated her dream again and again, as if to convince herself."
    new "Everything she was doing was worth it. Sarah repeated her dream again and again, as if to convince herself."

    old "It was another familiar voice that woke her up."
    new "It was another familiar voice that woke her up."

    old "Ladies and gentlemen!"
    new "Ladies and gentlemen!"

    old "His voice boomed out across the vast throne room."
    new "His voice boomed out across the vast throne room."

    old "Vaelen's voice was the kind that could bring a room to silence, a natural easy authority that seemed obvious to both the speaker and the listener."
    new "Vaelen's voice was the kind that could bring a room to silence, a natural easy authority that seemed obvious to both the speaker and the listener."

    old "I promise I won't hold up the celebrations for long!"
    new "I promise I won't hold up the celebrations for long!"

    old "Slowly, under some protest, the room grew quiet, until only Vaelen still spoke."
    new "Slowly, under some protest, the room grew quiet, until only Vaelen still spoke."

    old "Today, the Mythran army has succeeded in doing what no other empire or nation ever could, bring down the dynasty of Bagrad!"
    new "Today, the Mythran army has succeeded in doing what no other empire or nation ever could, bring down the dynasty of Bagrad!"

    old "Some cheers rang out."
    new "Some cheers rang out."

    old "For me and my company, it was an honour simply to fight besides you!"
    new "For me and my company, it was an honour simply to fight besides you!"

    old "We did most of the real fighting!"
    new "We did most of the real fighting!"

    old "Some laughter broke out, but Vaelen didn't let the interruption break his flow."
    new "Some laughter broke out, but Vaelen didn't let the interruption break his flow."

    old "But the reason I'm up here now is to ask you all to take a moment."
    new "But the reason I'm up here now is to ask you all to take a moment."

    old "Take a moment and join me in honouring a very special person."
    new "Take a moment and join me in honouring a very special person."

    old "One of my commanders, known to some of you as the Rose knight, but perhaps more recently as voidslayer!"
    new "One of my commanders, known to some of you as the Rose knight, but perhaps more recently as voidslayer!"

    old "She's got so many titles and names, it's hard to keep track!"
    new "She's got so many titles and names, it's hard to keep track!"

    old "The one and only, Sarah Rose!"
    new "The one and only, Sarah Rose!"

    old "Sarah grunted to herself as she heard the entire room explode into applause."
    new "Sarah grunted to herself as she heard the entire room explode into applause."

    old "She forced herself to her feet and akwardly waved around, receiving their praise all over again."
    new "She forced herself to her feet and akwardly waved around, receiving their praise all over again."

    old "Looking up, she could see Vaelen smiling at her."
    new "Looking up, she could see Vaelen smiling at her."

    old "That was their biggest difference, Sarah knew."
    new "That was their biggest difference, Sarah knew."

    old "Vaelen loved being up on the stage, to hear himself talk. Sarah hated almost every moment of it."
    new "Vaelen loved being up on the stage, to hear himself talk. Sarah hated almost every moment of it."

    old "I won't ask her to come up here and give a speech, I know she's not much for that, but I just wanted everyone to remember our hero!"
    new "I won't ask her to come up here and give a speech, I know she's not much for that, but I just wanted everyone to remember our hero!"

    old "The one who killed a monster, a demon!"
    new "The one who killed a monster, a demon!"

    old "More cheers rose up, echoing in the vast throne room, until applause and cheers seemed to be all there was."
    new "More cheers rose up, echoing in the vast throne room, until applause and cheers seemed to be all there was."

    old "Sarah continued to smile and wave, praying that it would soon be over."
    new "Sarah continued to smile and wave, praying that it would soon be over."

    old "Well, that's enough everyone, let's not embarrass her any further."
    new "Well, that's enough everyone, let's not embarrass her any further."

    old "The room grew silent again."
    new "The room grew silent again."

    old "Now, before we resume the party, I also wanted to leave you all with a gift!"
    new "Now, before we resume the party, I also wanted to leave you all with a gift!"

    old "A token of my generosity! A token of my gratitude! This is from me, Vaelen, to all of you!"
    new "A token of my generosity! A token of my gratitude! This is from me, Vaelen, to all of you!"

    old "Tonight it doesn't matter if you're one of my men or a loyal Mythran soldier, tonight we all share in the spoils!"
    new "Tonight it doesn't matter if you're one of my men or a loyal Mythran soldier, tonight we all share in the spoils!"

    old "Sarah watched as Vaelen clapped in his hand, signalling something to someone."
    new "Sarah watched as Vaelen clapped in his hand, signalling something to someone."

    old "Off to the side of the room, Sarah watched a soldier enter."
    new "Off to the side of the room, Sarah watched a soldier enter."

    old "In his hand, a chain, leading back."
    new "In his hand, a chain, leading back."

    old "Then she saw them enter."
    new "Then she saw them enter."

    old "All bound together by the chain, running from neck to neck, Sarah watched a parade of naked women being escorted into the room."
    new "All bound together by the chain, running from neck to neck, Sarah watched a parade of naked women being escorted into the room."

    old "The chain seemed to keep going on and on, more women dragged along, bound by their neck and hands to the great chain that pulled them all."
    new "The chain seemed to keep going on and on, more women dragged along, bound by their neck and hands to the great chain that pulled them all."

    old "All around her, Sarah could hear the soldiers beginning to jeer."
    new "All around her, Sarah could hear the soldiers beginning to jeer."

    old "Loud whistling noises rang out."
    new "Loud whistling noises rang out."

    old "These women here, my fine friends, aren't just any ladies."
    new "These women here, my fine friends, aren't just any ladies."

    old "With the women now closer, Sarah could see the fear in their eyes."
    new "With the women now closer, Sarah could see the fear in their eyes."

    old "All around them, she could see the ravenous appetite that filled the eyes of the soldiers that leered at them."
    new "All around them, she could see the ravenous appetite that filled the eyes of the soldiers that leered at them."

    old "They would be devoured."
    new "They would be devoured."

    old "These women are fine and proper royal ladies of the court of Bagrad."
    new "These women are fine and proper royal ladies of the court of Bagrad."

    old "Nobles, daughters of long and ancient bloodlines, accustomed to wearing the finest clothes!"
    new "Nobles, daughters of long and ancient bloodlines, accustomed to wearing the finest clothes!"

    old "Although, they seem to be without them for the moment!"
    new "Although, they seem to be without them for the moment!"

    old "The crowd roared with a cruel laughter."
    new "The crowd roared with a cruel laughter."

    old "This is my gift to you, my friends!"
    new "This is my gift to you, my friends!"

    old "Once these ladies would have considered you too low to even look you in the eyes!"
    new "Once these ladies would have considered you too low to even look you in the eyes!"

    old "But tonight, they will worship you like the heroes you are! Like the warriors you are! Like the conquerors of history that you are!"
    new "But tonight, they will worship you like the heroes you are! Like the warriors you are! Like the conquerors of history that you are!"

    old "The crowd grew wild with cheers."
    new "The crowd grew wild with cheers."

    old "Sarah had killed a beast from another world, but those cheers had seemed trivial compared to the pandemonium that Vaelen had unleashed."
    new "Sarah had killed a beast from another world, but those cheers had seemed trivial compared to the pandemonium that Vaelen had unleashed."

    old "He knew how to play a crowd."
    new "He knew how to play a crowd."

    old "And Sarah realized that this was what he wanted."
    new "And Sarah realized that this was what he wanted."

    old "To seize back control of these men's hearts. To remind them that he was one of them, and Sarah, despite everything, an outsider."
    new "To seize back control of these men's hearts. To remind them that he was one of them, and Sarah, despite everything, an outsider."

    old "Vaelen knew her position on the cruelty of war."
    new "Vaelen knew her position on the cruelty of war."

    old "He was challenging her to do something. To step up and put a stop to this."
    new "He was challenging her to do something. To step up and put a stop to this."

    old "But if she did step up and save these women, the soldiers would forever remember her as the woman that denied them their spoils of war."
    new "But if she did step up and save these women, the soldiers would forever remember her as the woman that denied them their spoils of war."

    old "She would forever alienate them from her."
    new "She would forever alienate them from her."

    old "They would never fight for her."
    new "They would never fight for her."

    old "And so Sarah remained quiet."
    new "And so Sarah remained quiet."

    old "But there is one more thing!"
    new "But there is one more thing!"

    old "Sarah felt her eyes drawn back to Vaelen again."
    new "Sarah felt her eyes drawn back to Vaelen again."

    old "A very special prize!"
    new "A very special prize!"

    old "Bring her out!"
    new "Bring her out!"

    old "On his command, a soldier entered the room with another chain, but to this one, only a single woman was bound."
    new "On his command, a soldier entered the room with another chain, but to this one, only a single woman was bound."

    old "Sarah looked upon her, her entire petite body, trembling like a leaf at the sight of this host of soldiers, leering at her."
    new "Sarah looked upon her, her entire petite body, trembling like a leaf at the sight of this host of soldiers, leering at her."

    old "The soldier dragged the woman all the way up to Vaelen and threw her down at his feet."
    new "The soldier dragged the woman all the way up to Vaelen and threw her down at his feet."

    old "Vaelen seized the chain and held the woman in her place."
    new "Vaelen seized the chain and held the woman in her place."

    old "Soldiers!"
    new "Soldiers!"

    old "Behold, the last daughter of a dead dynasty! Shah Mahda's daughter, Samayra!"
    new "Behold, the last daughter of a dead dynasty! Shah Mahda's daughter, Samayra!"

    old "The explosion of screams was louder than anything Sarah had ever heard in her life."
    new "The explosion of screams was louder than anything Sarah had ever heard in her life."

    old "The last of her lineage!"
    new "The last of her lineage!"

    old "And did I mention, a virgin?"
    new "And did I mention, a virgin?"

    old "More cruel laughter from the soldiers."
    new "More cruel laughter from the soldiers."

    old "The other ladies of the court are my gift to you, but for this one, I'm afraid, I must charge a price."
    new "The other ladies of the court are my gift to you, but for this one, I'm afraid, I must charge a price."

    old "Tell me, is there anyone out there who wants to start the bidding?"
    new "Tell me, is there anyone out there who wants to start the bidding?"

    old "Sarah could only look at the poor girl, too afraid to move, her eyes fixed to the floor."
    new "Sarah could only look at the poor girl, too afraid to move, her eyes fixed to the floor."

    old "Is this what she would have been, Sarah thought?"
    new "Is this what she would have been, Sarah thought?"

    old "Had she not escaped Rosanna in time, would she have ended up a slave like this girl? A thing to be used by soldiers for their cruel pleasures?"
    new "Had she not escaped Rosanna in time, would she have ended up a slave like this girl? A thing to be used by soldiers for their cruel pleasures?"

    old "Sarah felt as though she was sitting on the dais with her."
    new "Sarah felt as though she was sitting on the dais with her."

    old "Save Samayra, intercede"
    new "Save Samayra, intercede"

    old "The girl was too much like herself."
    new "The girl was too much like herself."

    old "Sarah realized she couldn't do nothing. If she walked away now, it would break her."
    new "Sarah realized she couldn't do nothing. If she walked away now, it would break her."

    old "Pulling herself up, Sarah stumbled half-drunk onto her feet."
    new "Pulling herself up, Sarah stumbled half-drunk onto her feet."

    old "Amidst the hollering and cheering, Sarah stumbled out onto the center of the room."
    new "Amidst the hollering and cheering, Sarah stumbled out onto the center of the room."

    old "She too knew how to command a room."
    new "She too knew how to command a room."

    old "Vaelen!"
    new "Vaelen!"

    old "The room went silent, save for some murmurs."
    new "The room went silent, save for some murmurs."

    old "Aah! Our hero!"
    new "Aah! Our hero!"

    old "I wanted to thank you for your kinds words."
    new "I wanted to thank you for your kinds words."

    old "I was simply speaking from the heart."
    new "I was simply speaking from the heart."

    old "You said I was a hero."
    new "You said I was a hero."

    old "Then I want to press my claim."
    new "Then I want to press my claim."

    old "Your claim?"
    new "Your claim?"

    old "As a loyal soldier, commander and, I suppose, demon killer, I think I am entitled to the spoils of war, more than any man here."
    new "As a loyal soldier, commander and, I suppose, demon killer, I think I am entitled to the spoils of war, more than any man here."

    old "Yes, I suppose that's true."
    new "Yes, I suppose that's true."

    old "Tell me what you want and you'll have it."
    new "Tell me what you want and you'll have it."

    old "Sarah raised her arm and pointed directly at Samayra."
    new "Sarah raised her arm and pointed directly at Samayra."

    old "Her."
    new "Her."

    old "I want her!"
    new "I want her!"

    old "For a moment, she could see Vaelen somewhat surprised at her request."
    new "For a moment, she could see Vaelen somewhat surprised at her request."

    old "Well, I meant what I said. You can have anything you want, so I guess that includes this one."
    new "Well, I meant what I said. You can have anything you want, so I guess that includes this one."

    old "Vaelen snapped his finger at the soldier."
    new "Vaelen snapped his finger at the soldier."

    old "Give the girl to Sarah."
    new "Give the girl to Sarah."

